member.returns:
            The subsets of the list. For example, if the input array is { 1, 2, 3 }, the output
            should be as follows:


{ 1 }

{ 2 }

{ 3 }

{ 1, 2 }

{ 1, 3 }

{ 2, 3 }

{ 1, 2, 3 }

            7 cases (without null set) in total.

member.summary:
Creates a  instance that iterates on each element.
Different with the default iteration operation, this type will iterate each element by reference,
in order that you can write the code like:

foreach (ref int element in new[] { 1, 3, 6, 10 }.EnumerateRef())
{
    Console.WriteLine(++element);
}

member.remarks:
We recommend you use this type like:

static int[] Example()
{
    using scoped var list = new ValueList<int>(10);
    list.Add(3);
    list.Add(6);
    return list.ToArray();
}

